{
  "local_port": 51874,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I keep getting dock connected on my Android, how do I get it off?",
  "response": "If you're experiencing a continuous \"dock connected\" notification or alert on your Android device, here are several steps you can take to resolve the issue:\n\n1. **Disconnect Any Accessories:**\n   - Ensure that there are no physical accessories (like docks or USB connections) attached to your device. Sometimes, a faulty connection can trigger this alert.\n\n2. **Check for Software Glitches:**\n   - Restart your phone. A simple reboot can sometimes resolve software issues.\n\n3. **Clear Apps Cache:**\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Apps** (or **Apps & notifications**) > **Show system** (if available) > Look for any app related to docks or accessories and clear the cache.\n\n4. **Check for USB Settings:**\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Connected devices** > **USB Preferences**, and ensure that it\u2019s set to \u201cNo data transfer\u201d if you\u2019re not using a dock.\n\n5. **Disable Docking Settings:**\n   - Some phones have specific settings related to dock mode (e.g., a \"Car Mode\" or \"Dock Mode\"). Check in **Settings** > **Display** or **Settings** > **Connections** for such options, and disable them if necessary.\n\n6. **Safe Mode:**\n   - Boot your device into Safe Mode to see if the issue persists. If it doesn't occur in Safe Mode, a third-party app may be the culprit. You can typically enter Safe Mode by holding down the power button, then long-pressing the \"Power off\" option and selecting \"OK\".\n\n7. **Update Software:**\n   - Ensure your device is running the latest version of Android. Go to **Settings** > **System** > **System updates**.\n\n8. **Factory Reset (Last Resort):**\n   - If all else fails and the issue continues, consider doing a factory reset. **Make sure to back up your data first**, as this will erase all personal data on your device. Go to **Settings** > **System** > **Reset options** > **Erase all data (factory reset)**.\n\nIf the problem persists after trying all these steps, it may be worth contacting your device's support or visiting a service center for further assistance.",
